which is easily obtained.

01:05:42.143 --> 01:05:43.443 position:41% line:83% align:start
[TUAN]
Hm...

01:05:43.477 --> 01:05:46.446 position:33% line:83% align:start
[GABRIELLE]
It's genetic programming.

01:05:46.480 --> 01:05:47.849 position:24% line:89% align:start
Consider a heron.

01:05:47.882 --> 01:05:50.550 position:19% line:83% align:start
If it doesn't eat the
fish it sees immediately,

01:05:50.584 --> 01:05:52.954 position:16% line:83% align:start
that fish will be eaten
by another heron.

01:05:52.987 --> 01:05:55.089 position:21% line:83% align:start
But, if another fish
doesn't come along,

01:05:55.123 --> 01:05:57.524 position:27% line:83% align:start
the first heron
starves to death.

01:05:57.557 --> 01:05:59.626 position:21% line:83% align:start
This is not survival
of the most fit.

01:05:59.660 --> 01:06:02.931 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's an ongoing conflict between
small short-term desires

01:06:02.964 --> 01:06:04.933 position:7% line:89% align:start
and larger long-term desires.

01:06:04.966 --> 01:06:08.568 position:21% line:83% align:start
An illogical game of
choice we call "will."

01:06:08.602 --> 01:06:10.071 position:30% line:83% align:start
In accordance
with this theory,

01:06:10.104 --> 01:06:12.673 position:19% line:83% align:start
even pain is something
we choose to feel.

01:06:12.706 --> 01:06:13.942 position:30% line:89% align:start
Explain that.

01:06:13.975 --> 01:06:15.043 position:33% line:83% align:start
[GABRIELLE]
The pain we experience

01:06:15.076 --> 01:06:17.946 position:19% line:83% align:start
the moment we prick a
finger is a feedback agent,

01:06:17.979 --> 01:06:20.480 position:13% line:83% align:start
a short-term desire trying
to leave an impression

01:06:20.514 --> 01:06:22.549 position:21% line:83% align:start
on the mind, and get
us to take action.

01:06:22.582 --> 01:06:24.618 position:10% line:89% align:start
Usually, to stop said pain.

01:06:24.651 --> 01:06:27.088 position:16% line:83% align:start
However, I'm sure you've
heard of instances where

01:06:27.121 --> 01:06:30.158 position:10% line:83% align:start
a machinist or construction
worker has sliced off a finger,

01:06:30.191 --> 01:06:31.993 position:27% line:83% align:start
and not noticed
right away because

01:06:32.026 --> 01:06:34.162 position:16% line:83% align:start
they were concentrating
on something else.

01:06:34.195 --> 01:06:36.830 position:19% line:83% align:start
This phenomenon occurs
when the agent for pain,

01:06:36.863 --> 01:06:39.533 position:16% line:83% align:start
competes with the agent
for focus and loses.

01:06:39.566 --> 01:06:42.971 position:16% line:83% align:start
Thus, the consciousness
delays giving it attention.

01:06:43.004 --> 01:06:45.672 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, our reality's not
shaped by our experiences,

01:06:45.706 --> 01:06:47.008 position:27% line:89% align:start
it's subjective.

01:06:47.041 --> 01:06:49.110 position:16% line:83% align:start
All the various feedback
agents in our brains

01:06:49.143 --> 01:06:50.510 position:5% line:89% align:start
shout at the top of their lungs

01:06:50.544 --> 01:06:52.879 position:24% line:83% align:start
and our minds only
listen to the loudest.

01:06:52.913 --> 01:06:55.049 position:21% line:83% align:start
That's a simplified
way of looking at it,

01:06:55.083 --> 01:06:57.851 position:27% line:83% align:start
but you seem to
grasp the concept.

01:06:57.884 --> 01:07:01.855 position:16% line:83% align:start
Before I go, I'd like to
ask your expert opinion.

01:07:01.888 --> 01:07:03.824 position:24% line:83% align:start
I assume you heard
the audio recording.

01:07:03.857 --> 01:07:05.559 position:27% line:83% align:start
Do you think the
threats are credible?

01:07:05.592 --> 01:07:07.794 position:27% line:83% align:start
Could they pull
